      "full_name": "Kakwavu Bukande Jérôme",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Former President of UCD/FAPC. FAPC’s control of illegal border posts between Uganda and the DRC – a key transit route for arms flows. As President of the FAPC, he exercised influence over policies and command and control over the activities of FAPC forces, which were involved in arms trafficking and, consequently, in violations of the arms embargo. According to the Office of the SRSG on Children and Armed Conflict, he was responsible for recruitment and use of children in Ituri in 2002. One of five senior FARDC officers who had been accused of serious crimes involving sexual violence and whose cases the Security Council had brought to the Government’s attention during its visit in 2009.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}